    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Raikes</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Hay</hi>: I have just received an answer from Lord
                    Lansdowne in which he desires me to say that His Majesty’s Government highly
                    appreciate the offer which has been made by the President, through you, to
                    convey the remains of Lord Pauncefote to England in a United States vessel, and
                    that they do not hesitate to accept ft on Lady Pauncefote’s behalf.</p>
                <p>Yours, very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur S. Raikes.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
